pr_body:
<!-- Please refer to CONTRIBUTING.md (https://github.com/fossology/fossology/blob/master/CONTRIBUTING.md)
before creating the pull request to make sure you follow all the standards. -->

## Description

As a part of **GSoC 2020 Fossology.**
New Feature - FossDash: Fossdash helps to extract meaningful data from fossology_DB and exported those metrics to the time series Influx database.  Grafana query tool used to query those metrics and visualized them with the help of charts and graphs in the Dashboard.

Wants to know more about it. Checkout Wiki of FossDash :: https://github.com/darshank15/GSoC_2020_FOSSOlogy/wiki

### Changes

* Added Fossology configuration in the UI page.
  * `src/lib/php/fossdash-config.php`
  * `src/www/ui/admin-fossdash-config.php`
* Wrote a fossdash-publisher script in python to get the latest data from Postgres and convert them to InfluxDB standard formate and then push them to InfluxDB.
  * `install/fossdash/fossdash-publish.py.in`

*Some Bootstrap UI changes in
  * `src/www/ui/admin-config.php`
  * `src/lib/php/common-sysconfig.php`

## How to test
 * Unit-test for PHP
   * `src/lib/php/tests/test_fossdash_config.php`

pr_title: Added influxDB authentication and new latest fossdash Dashboard
pr_body:
As a part of **GSoC 2020 Fossology**.
* Added influxDB authentication by enabling username and password 
* Added new dashboard as default provisioning dashboard in grafana.
* Added new instance-specific Dashboard, Having a dropdown list of Instances, And you can now select an instance and see the Details of that specific instance on a Dashboard.
* Grafana plugin installation on startup in a docker container.
* Source installation script for grafana and influxdb.
